summary: “Yee-haw is having a moment this year,” as Kacey told the crowd this summer at Madison Square Garden, opening for Harry Styles....
text: Yee-haw is having a moment this year,” as Kacey told the crowd this summer at Madison Square Garden, opening for Harry Styles. (This double bill was basically a D-Day assault on the Normandy of my soul, right up to the moment they sang a duet on Shania’s “You’re Still the One.” Still recovering.) “Slow Burn” digs deep into the stoner twang-drone of a spaced cowgirl, oddly reminiscent of David Gilmour in his pastoral psychedelic watching-cows mode. Since Kacey songs about Kacey are always better than Kacey songs about other people, she’s at her most masterful in “Slow Burn”: “Texas is hot, I can be cold, Grandma cried when I pierced my nose.

summary: Harry & Y/N try to get pregnant  pt.2
body:
Harry & Y/N try to get pregnant pt.2

____

Here is part one

____

“We’re pregnant!”

Everyone was immediately cheering and hugging Jane, one of Harry’s childhood friends.

Only it took Harry and Y/N a moment to crack a smile.

“Congratulations, I’m really happy for the two of you,” Harry smiled at Jane and her fiancé.

They aren’t even married yet, Y/N thought.

“Yeah,” Y/N smiled from across the table. “Congratulations guys. Uh—you’re going to be wonderful,” she smiled, on the verge of tears as she excused herself.

Harry followed her, and caught her just in time to hear her sniffling and see her arm come up as she wiped her tears.

“Hey. Baby,” Harry tried quietly to get her attention as she made her way to the bathroom of Jane’s home. Harry swiftly followed her in, closing the door behind himself. “Darling, please don’t cry.”

“It’s not fair, Harry,” she whined through her tears. “We’ve been trying for months.”

“I know, Y/N. Our time will come, okay? I promise,” he hugged her as she cried.

“I just wanna have a baby,” she cried sadly.

-6 months later-

“Yeah, I’ve got an interview tomorrow morning but after that I’m totally free,” Harry was conversating with his mother, who wanted him to accompany her to a cat shelter tomorrow afternoon.

Harry was leaning against the kitchen counter, but stood up straight when he heard his name being whimpered by Y/N as she walked towards him quickly, tears in her eyes.

“Hey, what’s the matter?” Harry asked, concerned as she wrapped her arms around his waist and cried into his chest, her shoulder bobbing up and down.

“Why are you crying, hm?” Harry whispered, holding her close.

“I’m s-sorry,” she cried into his chest. “I’m sorry I keep letting you down.”

Then it clicked. She took a pregnancy test this morning, and they had been waiting for the results.

“It was another no?” Harry asked, and when she nodded, in tears, Harry’s eyes watered too.

“It’s not your fault,” he said quickly, pulling her jnto another hug.

“Yes it is,” she cried. “It’s my fault it doesn’t work. We’ve been trying for so long and,” she cried. “It just doesn’t work. I’m sorry. I know how bad you want this, I just don’t know what’s wrong with me,” she was crying hysterically and Harry didn’t even have time to explain to Anne what was going on.

“No, stop it,” Harry cupped her cheeks. “Hey, look at me,” he cooed as she looked down, ashamed. “Mine of this is your fault. We’ve both been trying, yeah? Hasn’t worked? ‘s nobody’s fault, bubba,” he cooed. “All we can do is keep trying. Okay?” He asked as she cried more, a long sigh leaving her mouth as tears steamed down her cheeks.

Harry kissed her lips, cupping her face still. “It’ll happen. I promise, okay? It’s going to happen. ‘s just taking a little bit longer for us, okay? But it’s not your fault. You’re perfect, y’hear me?” He hummed, holding her close to him, his hand tangled in her hair as he kissed her head a few times.

“It’s been over twelve months, Harry. That’s a whole year,” she cried. “When? I want it to happen now,” she cried.

“I know,” Harry closed his eyes and felt he warm tears seep out. “I know, my baby but we have to be patient, okay? Hm?”

——

Harry was sat playing his guitar, trying to figure out which tune was best for this new beat he had created for his album.

“Harry!” He heard Y/N scream.

A second later she was running into his music room (really, it was just a room with rugs, sound proof walls, and bean bags, and a couch.) Harry stood up and put his guitar to the side as she ran into his arms.

She was taking another pregnancy test earlier.

“It’s okay. We’ll keep trying-“ he began, his chest heavy already. It’s been a year of nothing.

“No,” Y/N cried, holding the pregnancy test up. “I’m pregnant, baby! We did it!”

Harry audibly gasped, his eyes wide as he took the pregnancy test from her hands. Once he saw the word ‘pregnant’ he lost it. The test was dropped and he picked up his wife instead, spinning her around and kissing her lips multiple times, over and over again.

“We did it! Oh my—“ he laughed loudly. “We did it, Y/N! Oh, my love,” he cried as he hugged her. “My love,” he cried. “We’re going to have a little baby,” he laughed through his tears. “I love you so much. I knew we’d do it,” he was then getting on his knees. He pushed her shirt up and left wet kisses all over her stomach. “We’re gonna have a baby,” he said excitedly before he was standing again, holding Y/N’s face between his big hands and pressing a loud, wet kiss to her lips. Then another. “I love you,” he smiled before giving her another obnoxious kiss. “I love you so much,” he kissed her again, holding her face as tightly as he could with out hurting her.

“We’re gonna have a baby,” she cried.

“What month is it?” Harry grinned, sniffling. “We’re in June….that’s…aw, we’re going to have a March baby!”

“A little March baby!” Y/N cooed. “Oh, hopefully it’s still a little chilly so we can dress them in warm sweaters and wrap them up in little blankies everywhere we go,” Y/N spoke hopefully as Harry wiped her tears.

——

“Harry and I are having a baby!” Y/N cheered, at a small dinner that consisted only of Harry, Anne, Gemma, her boyfriend, Y/N’s siblings, and Y/N’s parents.

Anne (having experienced first hand how upset they were that they couldn’t conceive) immediately had tears in her eyes as she gasped, standing from the table and walking over to the two. “Congratulations! Oh, you two are going to make the perfect parents! I love you both so much! Congratulations,” she laughed, hugging the both of them at one time.

Everyone was clapping and cooing and cheering, and Y/N was overjoyed.

She’s pregnant!

There’s going to be a little tiny baby here soon, half of her, and half of him.

She was over the moon.

“Can’t believe it. We’re going to be parents,” Harry grinned, hugging her.

Just the word, in reference to her and Harry, made her begin to cry. “You’re going to be the most amazing dad, Harry,” she cried.

“Me?” He laughed softly through his tears. “You’re going to a phenomenal mummy, baby,” he laughed, sniffling before kissing her lips, his hand on her tummy that he couldn’t wait to see grow.

Everyone was immediately cheering and hugging Jane, one of Harry’s childhood friends.

Only it took Harry and Y/N a moment to crack a smile.

“Congratulations, I’m really happy for the two of you,” Harry smiled at Jane and her fiancé.

They aren’t even married yet, Y/N thought.

“Yeah,” Y/N smiled from across the table. “Congratulations guys. Uh—you’re going to be wonderful,” she smiled, on the verge of tears as she excused herself.

Harry followed her, and caught her just in time to hear her sniffling and see her arm come up as she wiped her tears.

“Hey. Baby,” Harry tried quietly to get her attention as she made her way to the bathroom of Jane’s home. Harry swiftly followed her in, closing the door behind himself. “Darling, please don’t cry.”

“It’s not fair, Harry,” she whined through her tears. “We’ve been trying for months.”

“I know, Y/N. Our time will come, okay? I promise,” he hugged her as she cried.

“I just wanna have a baby,” she cried sadly.

“Why are you crying, hm?” Harry whispered, holding her close.

“I’m s-sorry,” she cried into his chest. “I’m sorry I keep letting you down.”

“It was another no?” Harry asked, and when she nodded, in tears, Harry’s eyes watered too.

“We have to make a phone call!” Harry screamed before laughing as he and Y/N ran up the stairs and straight to his childhood bedroom.

Harry locked the door and while he did that Y/N was removing her red dress, pulling her tights down as well (her heels had been removed within the first two hours of the party).

Harry took off his shirt, unbuttoning his jeans and letting them fall to his ankles before the two kissed, falling onto Harry’s twin sized bed.

“Mhm,” she hummed, wrapping her arms around his neck.

Harry breathed deeply as he removed her underwear, then his own. He rubbed himself up against her clit a few times before he was inside of her, the two moaning at the familiar yet still amazing feeling.

“Gotta admit,” Harry groaned as he thrusted. “The trying has been fun.”

Fun, yes. But it’s also been exhausting. And not just physically.

The two were mentally drained. It’s been six months of constant sex. Running to the nearest bedroom, bathroom—hell it was even a closet once.

They want a baby.

“I love yeh, baby but need you to keep it down, yeah?”

After that, Y/N layed with her legs crossed tightly, ensuring that none of his come leaked out. (Harry spent that time kissing her cheeks and neck and breasts, mumbling how much he loved her and how they would never stop trying no matter what).

After a solid five minutes they got dressed again, going downstairs to find everyone in the same yelling fit that they’d left them in.

“Okay, you’re free,” Y/N laughed, and so did Harry.

“Come here,” he didn’t let go of her hand (theirs were interlocked) and pulled her with him to the couch. He pulled her onto his lap, kissing her cheek a few times.

“I love you,” he said softly as she layed comfortably on the couch, her head resting on Harry’s chest now as she sighed and smiled up at him.

“I love you too.”

“We need you, Harry!” Gemma screamed. “Mum’s rubbish at this!”

“Hey!” Anne was shocked.

“I’m sitting this round out,” Harry laughed before looking down to his beautiful wife, whom he so desperately wants a baby with. He pushed some of her hair aaay from her face. “You’re beautiful,” he said softly.

She smiled, kissing his wrist that was near her face since he’d been cupping her cheek.

“Hope our baby looks like you,” Harry mumbled.

blog.description: Koda. 24. He/Him. Biracial. Gay. If I wasn’t a college student in South Carolina, then I’d be a cryptid, happily living in the Pacific Northwest.

summary: Can’t believe I’ve gotten hate for telling people to vote Chadwick Boseman for  best dressed instead of Harry Styles.  I’m a...
body:
Can’t believe I’ve gotten hate for telling people to vote Chadwick Boseman for best dressed instead of Harry Styles. I’m a massive fan of both but here’s why I voted for Chadwick.

1. He’s not white and my biracial ass wanted to celebrate that.

2. He’s a fellow South Carolinian. I grew up 15 minutes from Anderson, his hometown.

3. Harry has dozens of best dressed awards and with the looks Chadwick has served this year, he deserves to win.
